{"author":{"id":"c52cb19fb02c210e51792121b2bae318d19fa8efb308ae796946bf1f79891ad1"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1781996727,"nonce":"e5wtJ75tTyz9KI4ZP+29ybYUnT4=","title":"Add Common Table Expressions: `WITH name AS (…) SELECT …`, then `WITH RECURSIVE`.","message":"- v1: non-recursive single/multiple CTEs referenced as FROM/join sources.\n- Deferred: `WITH RECURSIVE` (self-reference + UNION; depends on set-ops issue).\n\n- Builder: name a subquery and reference it as a source, e.g.\n  `conn.with::\u003cName\u003e(|sub| …)…from_cte::\u003cName\u003e()…`. Exact surface TBD during\n  design.\n- Type-level: a CTE introduces a NEW named source whose projection shape derives\n  from the inner query's `Row`; referencing it needs a new `SourceSpec` kind (a\n  named reference, not a table). The `q{depth}_{index}` alias machinery and the\n  `RenderSubquery` infra (from subqueries) are the building blocks.\n- Rendering: emit the `WITH name AS (…)[, …]` prefix before the main SELECT; CTE\n  bodies render first, with shared param numbering (borrowed `Renderer`).\n- Recursive form: self-reference inside the CTE body + `UNION [ALL]` between the\n  base and recursive terms — build on the set-ops work.\n\ncrates/squealy/src/query.rs (CTE source kind, naming, WITH plumbing), render.rs +\nsquealy-test/src/sql.rs, lib.rs, + tests.\n\nRender (single + multiple CTEs, CTE referenced in FROM and in a join), bind\nordering (CTE bodies first), per-backend, `#[ignore]` round-trip; recursive CTE\nas a follow-up.\n\nLarge (~one+ session) — new source kind + WITH rendering; recursive is a further\nincrement.\n\nSet operations (issue) for the recursive variant.","files":null}]}